  "riddle": "1. A place dedicated to the beauty and intricacies of nature's crystals exists in a city known for its artistic endeavors — how many languages are spoken there?\n\n2. Ascend to the realm where the stunning specimens rest; what is the elevation in meters of this crystal haven?\n\n3. Among the many who admire this museum, what rating do visitors give it based on their experiences?\n\n4. Combine the height above sea level you uncovered in clue 2 with the appreciation score from clue 3. What numerical sum do you reach?\n\n5. In a distant land, a dinosaur with a name echoing the sands of Egypt made its first appearance in scientific literature — which year did this prehistoric marvel first grace our understanding?\n\n6. A vessel once traversed the seas, bearing the name of a celebrated navigational tool. What was the measurement of its length?\n\n7. The location of a theater renowned for creativity lies where stories come to life — in which city and state can you find it?\n\n8. Exploring nearby, how many stadiums provide entertainment in the vicinity of this urban cultural gem?\n\n9. The name of the theatrical institution you found in clue 7 holds hidden vowels. Can you count the number of vowels within that name?\n\n10. Now, for your final challenge, compute the digital root of the function formed by taking the elevation from clue 2, adding the total from clue 4, joining the length from clue 6, and concluding with the count of stadiums from clue 8. The formula to follow is: digital_root(clue 2 + clue 4 + clue 6 + clue 8). What single-digit answer do you find?",
